subSubSection.paragraph:
Genitalia
. Median lobe thin, elongate, constricted on lateral margins; ventral valve sclerotized, apex bent ventrally, with one large seta on either side of midline and 3 small setae near lateral margins; dorsal valve less sclerotized, rounded apically; only apical 0.5 of internal sac with armature, most of apical 0.25 lined with fine scales and remaining 0.25 lined with small spinules (
Fig. 14
). Lateral lobes elongate, cleft to 0.2 their length, apex of lobes more strongly sclerotized, with strong setae at apex of lobes (
Fig. 15
).
